Art once again you have written some though povoking words. as SW has said, Is this the real Art? Awesome post. More!! <br>
I wonder why Rock Marines operated that way? Could it have been because they were well aware of the communist method of operation and the sickness, destruction and results of communist domonition as they had experieicnce in their own country?<br>
I knew when they accompanied us on operations we were going to get some straight scoop from the prisioners we captured and usually did. <br><br>
I'll like to see what are the symtoms, of PTSD. If anyone has that info,  I'll like to see it posted on top as Art has mentioned.<br><br>
The beauty of all of our communications is found in the overall character of those who have posted from their hearts. i've seen a lot of plastic covering and it's only now that I am beginning to see the raw human element behind the postings. Seemed like all up till the past few weeks it was all nothing more then a shadow of the real thing. people trying to impress others by knowledge gained after the fact. Information obtained years after the tour. But what was it like then what were we thinking then and how and why we responded the way we did. That's what has been missing.<br><br>
Here's an interesting note. Why has the Vietnam vet not joined service organizations like the VFW, American Legion and others like those before us have? Korean and WWII veterans continue to dominate those organizations but why has the Viet vet stayed away from those organizations. Why was it necessary for Viet Vets to begin their own service organizations?<br><br>
Speaking about Jane Fonda, The VFW I lend my name to so they could open up a new chapter here, I've only been there two- three times has a nice picture of Jane in the mens head. Pasted right there at the bottom of the piss tube. I think that's the only reason I ever visited the place.<br>

